'''''The Attack''''' is a [[multidirectional shooter]] video game created, designed, and implemented by Jim Pettingell for the [[TI-99/4A]] home computer and published by [[Texas Instruments]] in 1981.<ref name="giantlist"/> The game was  developed at [[Milton Bradley Company|Milton Bradley]] as ''Alien Attack'', inspired by the movies ''[[Alien (film)|Alien]]'' (1979) and ''[[Barbarella (film)|Barbarella]]'' (1968). After being sold to TI, the name was changed to ''The Attack''.<ref>{{cite web|title=TI-99/4A Videogame House - The Attack|url=http://www.videogamehouse.net/theattack.html|website=www.videogamehouse.net|accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
The player flies a spaceship in four directions around a single screen, shooting "spores", which connect together to form new aliens, and already formed aliens before they eat the player. Incubators, shown as square boxes, release more spores or, in later levels, aliens.<ref name=manual/>

There are four skill levels: Novice, Intermediate, Master, and Pro.<ref name=manual/>

